issues.body:
### Steps to reproduce

1. Create a TextFormField wrapped with a Semantics widget.
2. Add a label and set excludeSemantics: true.
3. Run on Flutter Web using flutter build web.
4. Try to inspect the generated <input> element.
5. Observe that aria-label, it will come as 'Login_email' which is provided in Semantics Label
6. Now set excludeSemantics: false and run the Flutter web.
7. Try to inspect the generated <input> element
8. Observe the aria-label, it will come as 'Email', which is the hint text provided in the TextFormField. 'Login_email' label is not coming in this case

Tested on Chrome stable version 138.0.7204.101

### Expected results

- The <input> should have aria-label="Login_email" so it can be used in web automation tools like Selenium/Cypress.

- Excluding the child semantics should still allow mapping the label (i.e 'Login_email' in my case) to the native input.

### Actual results

- Input cannot be typed into programmatically (via Playwright/Selenium/Cypress) in flutter web when excludeSemantics is set to true.

- If excludeSemantics: false, aria-label is coming as 'Email' (which is Hint text in InputDecoration of TextFormField, not the one which I am providing in labels of Semantics widget ) and input is interactive in flutter web. We can't use Hint text as semantics label as we are using language support and Hint Text can be changed based on selected language.

### Code sample

<details open><summary>Code sample</summary>

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter/semantics.dart';

void main() {
  runApp(const MyApp());
  Future.delayed(const Duration(seconds: 20), () {
    SemanticsBinding.instance.ensureSemantics();
  });
}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return MaterialApp(
      title: 'Semantics Bug Demo',
      home: Scaffold(
        appBar: AppBar(title: const Text('Semantics Bug')),
        body: const Center(
          child: Padding(
            padding: EdgeInsets.all(16.0),
            child: LoginForm(),
          ),
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

class LoginForm extends StatefulWidget {
  const LoginForm({super.key});

  @override
  State<LoginForm> createState() => _LoginFormState();
}

class _LoginFormState extends State<LoginForm> {
  final _formKey = GlobalKey<FormState>();
  final TextEditingController _emailController = TextEditingController();
  final FocusNode _emailFocusNode = FocusNode();

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    return Form(
      key: _formKey,
      child: Semantics(
        label: 'Login_email',
        container: true,
        excludeSemantics: true,
        explicitChildNodes: true,
        textField: true,
        enabled: true,
        child: TextFormField(
          controller: _emailController,
          focusNode: _emailFocusNode,
          decoration: const InputDecoration(
            hintText: 'Email',
          ),
          validator: (value) {
            if (_emailFocusNode.hasFocus) return null;
            if (value == null || value.isEmpty) return 'Email is required';
            return null;
          },
        ),
      ),
    );
  }
}

```

</details>


