If the navigator page stack contains more than one page, and a page that is not the one displayed requests focus through autofocus, that focus should be delayed until the page is put on the forefront and the focus should stay on the currently viewed page until then.


# Repro

Here is a repro repository https://github.com/cedvdb/flutter_repros/tree/autofocus (checkout the autofocus branch)

When you run the app and click on the button you'll see the focus disappear from the page that is shown because the underlying page hides the `TextFormField` for a second then respawns it.


Alternatively here is the repro code which needs the rxdart dep

