After testing, it was discovered that the Sogou Pinyin input method on the Windows platform does not display the Pinyin in the text box during the user input process. As a result, `composingRange` remains ineffective. This leads to passing incorrect parameters when calling the `setComposingRect` function.

```dart
// Original code:
final int offset = composingRange.isValid ? composingRange.start : 0;

// Modified code:
final int offset = composingRange.isValid ? composingRange.start : _value.selection.baseOffset;
```

This can solve some of the issues. However, after making these changes, the candidate selection box of Sogou Pinyin input method obstructs half of the text's height. My temporary solution was to offset it downwards by half of the line height.

I hope this issue can be fixed soon, as the Sogou Pinyin input method has the highest usage rate in the China region.

